are going to turn
the trick.

719
00:30:32,446 --> 00:30:35,348
Well, now, I wasn't sent here
by the State Department,
Mr. President.

720
00:30:35,422 --> 00:30:37,332
I was asked to come here
by our friend in Houston.

721
00:30:37,406 --> 00:30:39,510
So this is
a courtesy call.

722
00:30:39,582 --> 00:30:43,292
I don't need courtesy.
I need airplanes,
guns and money.

723
00:30:43,359 --> 00:30:47,864
Well, we just doubled
the CIA budget
for covert ops...

724
00:30:47,933 --> 00:30:49,307
From 5 million
to 10 million.

725
00:30:49,374 --> 00:30:51,284
That's right.
Is that a joke?

726
00:30:52,574 --> 00:30:54,581
No.
Is that meant
to be a funny joke?

727
00:30:54,654 --> 00:30:55,602
No, sir.

728
00:30:55,679 --> 00:30:57,403
ZIA: Congressman,
what they're saying is

729
00:30:57,470 --> 00:31:00,984
$10 million from the U.S.
To fight the Russian Army

730
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:04,539
is such a low figure
that it can be mistaken
for a joke.

731
00:31:04,608 --> 00:31:08,184
I caught up to the
sarcasm there, sir.
Let me be clear.

732
00:31:09,150 --> 00:31:11,222
The United States is
eager to assist you.

733
00:31:11,295 --> 00:31:12,309
No, you're not.
You're not.

734
00:31:12,382 --> 00:31:14,008
Absolutely not.
I went to Oxford

735
00:31:14,079 --> 00:31:15,322
and I know what
that word means.

736
00:31:15,390 --> 00:31:17,529
The U.S. Is not eager
to assist us.

737
00:31:17,598 --> 00:31:20,348
Well, now it's
my understanding that we
offered to sell you F-16s.

738
00:31:20,414 --> 00:31:21,363
You didn't want them.

739
00:31:21,438 --> 00:31:23,032
Because you refused
to sell us the radar.

740
00:31:23,103 --> 00:31:24,311
RASHID: So to hell with that.

741
00:31:24,381 --> 00:31:27,578
ZIA: And this is emblematic
of American fence sitting

742
00:31:27,645 --> 00:31:29,075
when it comes
to fighting the Soviets.

743
00:31:29,150 --> 00:31:31,964
To hell with it!
You sell us the planes
but not the radar.

744
00:31:32,030 --> 00:31:35,064
You offer Afghans rifles
from the First World War

745
00:31:35,455 --> 00:31:38,619
while Soviet helicopters
are killing everything
they can find,

746
00:31:38,687 --> 00:31:41,207
people, animals,
food supplies.
So to hell with it!

747
00:31:41,278 --> 00:31:43,449
Yeah.
You sell
the Israelis the radar,

748
00:31:43,518 --> 00:31:45,427
so that's why he says,
"To hell with it."

749
00:31:45,502 --> 00:31:47,542
Again, I understood. Yeah.

750
00:31:47,741 --> 00:31:51,038
Also, the arms and funding
should flow through us.

751
00:31:53,023 --> 00:31:54,005
I'm sorry?

752
00:31:54,079 --> 00:31:55,737
That's been part
of the problem.

753
00:31:55,807 --> 00:31:58,229
The arms and the funding
should flow through us.

754
00:31:58,303 --> 00:32:00,822
We have experience
with warfare of this kind.

755
00:32:00,894 --> 00:32:03,709
And your CIA has
an unimpressive
track record.

756
00:32:03,774 --> 00:32:05,847
Oh. I wouldn't say that.

757
00:32:05,919 --> 00:32:09,661
They missed 130,000
Soviet soldiers walking
into Afghanistan.

758
00:32:10,655 --> 00:32:12,216
Okay, we blew that call.

759
00:32:12,287 --> 00:32:13,750
I would say so.

760
00:32:17,406 --> 00:32:23,386
Well, I don't want
to use up any more
of your hospitality,

761
00:32:23,455 --> 00:32:28,126
so I will take
your message back
to my committee chairman,

762
00:32:28,192 --> 00:32:30,875
and we will give it
our fullest attention.

763
00:32:31,071 --> 00:32:33,112
Let me walk you
to the door.

764
00:32:34,656 --> 00:32:35,603
(OFFICER SHOUTS COMMAND)

765
00:32:37,790 --> 00:32:40,279
I learned about you
before you came here.

766
00:32:40,351 --> 00:32:43,515
I learned that you're a man
of many character flaws.

767
00:32:43,712 --> 00:32:44,759
I am.

768
00:32:44,863 --> 00:32:46,871
But I also learned
that you never
promise anything

769
00:32:46,944 --> 00:32:48,603
you cannot deliver.

770
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,394
No, I don't,
Mr. President.

771
00:32:50,464 --> 00:32:51,893
Then promise me this.

772
00:32:51,968 --> 00:32:54,934
Go to Peshawar
and see the refugee camps.

773
00:32:55,263 --> 00:32:56,823
Right now. Today.

774
00:32:57,311 --> 00:32:59,995
Go to Peshawar and see
with your own eyes.

775
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:02,776
I have a helicopter
waiting to take you.

776
00:33:03,647 --> 00:33:05,435
All right, l'll do it.

777
00:33:05,696 --> 00:33:07,157
Thank you,
Mr. Congressman.

778
00:33:07,231 --> 00:33:08,475
Mr. President.

779
00:33:13,854 --> 00:33:15,742
All right, you,
come on.

780
00:33:18,047 --> 00:33:19,127
How did it go?

781
00:33:19,199 --> 00:33:20,409
Well, there were
three of them.

782
00:33:20,479 --> 00:33:23,480
It was like getting slapped
around by a Pakistani
vaudeville team.

783
00:33:23,551 --> 00:33:24,828
You know
you've pretty much
hit rock bottom

784
00:33:24,896 --> 00:33:26,522
when you've been told
you have character flaws
by a man

785
00:33:26,592 --> 00:33:29,460
who hanged his predecessor
in a military coup.

786
00:33:29,534 --> 00:33:30,484
Can we go home now?

787
00:33:30,559 --> 00:33:33,112
No. No, we have
to make one more stop.

788
00:34:30,208 --> 00:34:31,582
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

789
00:35:16,415 --> 00:35:18,139
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

790
00:35:24,289 --> 00:35:25,849
I've seen enough.

791
00:35:28,449 --> 00:35:32,726
About 350 people
in three small villages
at Kandahar.

792
00:35:32,802 --> 00:35:35,669
But instead of doing
it all at once,

793
00:35:35,744 --> 00:35:38,078
the Russians would
make the parents watch

794
00:35:38,144 --> 00:35:40,533
as they slit
the throats
of the children.

795
00:35:40,609 --> 00:35:42,649
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

796
00:35:43,969 --> 00:35:50,364
So, the Russians
gathered all the defectors
and piled them like wood

797
00:35:50,434 --> 00:35:52,537
in the center
of the village.

798
00:35:53,089 --> 00:35:55,325
Then they ran over them
with their tanks.

799
00:35:55,392 --> 00:35:57,116
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

800
00:35:57,985 --> 00:36:01,564
WOMAN TRANSLATOR: I saw
something shiny on the ground.
I thought it was a toy.

801
00:36:03,778 --> 00:36:07,095
When I reached down
to grab it, it exploded
in my hand.

802
00:36:07,970 --> 00:36:09,310
I should have known.

803
00:36:09,377 --> 00:36:14,198
Because last year
my little brother tried
to pick up a piece of candy.

804
00:36:15,809 --> 00:36:17,533
It split him in half.

805
00:36:18,209 --> 00:36:21,722
It takes more work to take
care of a wounded child
than a dead one.

806
00:36:21,794 --> 00:36:24,512
So when the Russians
cover fields with toy mines,

807
00:36:24,578 --> 00:36:28,635
adults who might help
with the war effort have
to take care of the children.

808
00:36:28,705 --> 00:36:30,778
BONNIE: You can see yourself.

809
00:36:31,778 --> 00:36:32,792
Like a bug.

810
00:36:32,865 --> 00:36:33,813
(BUZZING)

811
00:36:34,177 --> 00:36:35,454
(WOMAN TRANSLATING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

812
00:36:37,825 --> 00:36:39,418
They're beautiful.

813
00:36:40,258 --> 00:36:42,397
How many children
do you have?

814
00:36:44,545 --> 00:36:45,853
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

815
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:47,902
She had six.

816
00:36:50,049 --> 00:36:52,831
So, what do you want to be
when you grow up?

817
00:37:00,899 --> 00:37:02,621
(SOBBING)

