00:37:32,803 --> 00:37:37,244
Hi. I have Congressman Wilson
here to see the station
chief, Harold Holt.

819
00:37:37,315 --> 00:37:39,899
Down the hall.
Second door on the left.

820
00:37:40,514 --> 00:37:42,041
L'll wait outside.

821
00:37:43,330 --> 00:37:45,152
Look, normally,
a congressional delegation,

822
00:37:45,217 --> 00:37:48,480
we'd give them a courtesy
briefing on the situation,
but as you can see,

823
00:37:48,547 --> 00:37:51,776
it's getting pretty late,
we don't have a whole lot
of time anyway, so...

824
00:37:51,842 --> 00:37:53,534
Well, make the time.
Huh?

825
00:37:54,371 --> 00:37:56,955
Fuck your time, Harold.
I'm on Defense Appropriations.

826
00:37:57,026 --> 00:37:59,776
I'm catching a plane
back to Washington
in just a few minutes.

827
00:37:59,842 --> 00:38:02,876
Now, I need a full
classified briefing
right now.

828
00:38:06,435 --> 00:38:08,224
Hundred and twenty thousand
Soviet troops in all.

829
00:38:08,291 --> 00:38:09,240
Hundred and twenty thousand?

830
00:38:09,315 --> 00:38:11,388
40th Army is garrisoned
in the cities

831
00:38:11,459 --> 00:38:12,572
and in the airports.

832
00:38:12,644 --> 00:38:15,196
Your seventh and eighth
infantry divisions
are in Kabul.

833
00:38:15,267 --> 00:38:17,918
The 18th in Mazar-e Sharif,
the fourth armored...

834
00:38:17,987 --> 00:38:18,935
Anything inside?

835
00:38:19,011 --> 00:38:20,058
I'm sorry?

836
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:21,723
They controlling
anything inside?

837
00:38:21,795 --> 00:38:23,322
Soviet advisors
have appropriated

838
00:38:23,394 --> 00:38:25,467
the Afghan intel service
and the ministries.

839
00:38:25,538 --> 00:38:26,913
Which ministries?

840
00:38:26,979 --> 00:38:28,320
All of them.

841
00:38:28,643 --> 00:38:32,733
Anyway, the fourth armored
covers Bagram Airbase.

842
00:38:32,802 --> 00:38:33,980
Seventh Armored is...

843
00:38:34,050 --> 00:38:36,733
Why ain't they shooting down
them helicopters?

844
00:38:36,802 --> 00:38:37,981
I'm sorry?

845
00:38:38,050 --> 00:38:39,610
The helicopters, Harold.

846
00:38:39,682 --> 00:38:42,979
Why ain't we giving them
something to shoot down
them helicopters?

847
00:38:43,043 --> 00:38:46,392
The helicopters
are a problem.

848
00:38:48,227 --> 00:38:49,503
You think?

849
00:38:50,274 --> 00:38:52,510
Congressman...
They're shooting
at Soviet gunships

850
00:38:52,577 --> 00:38:56,123
with Enfield rifles.
That's basically what
Davy Crockett used.

851
00:38:56,194 --> 00:38:58,912
The Soviet Hind gunship
is especially armor plated
to resist bullets.

852
00:38:58,979 --> 00:39:02,776
Yeah, I know, I know.
So you tell me what you
need to shoot them down.

853
00:39:02,851 --> 00:39:03,799
What do you mean?

854
00:39:03,876 --> 00:39:05,534
Tell me what you need.

855
00:39:06,723 --> 00:39:07,768
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

856
00:39:07,842 --> 00:39:11,552
You tell me what you need,
and I will go about
getting it for you.

857
00:39:11,618 --> 00:39:13,855
Congressman, I appreciate
your generosity,

858
00:39:13,923 --> 00:39:18,593
but a sudden influx of money
and modern weaponry
would draw attention.

859
00:39:19,460 --> 00:39:21,881
What?
A sudden influx
of money and modern...

860
00:39:21,956 --> 00:39:23,899
Wait, it would
draw attention?

861
00:39:23,972 --> 00:39:24,954
Yeah.

862
00:39:25,859 --> 00:39:28,346
Why, I don't even know
what that means.

863
00:39:28,419 --> 00:39:30,109
This is the Cold War.
Everybody knows about it.

864
00:39:30,179 --> 00:39:31,194
Should I continue
with the briefing?

865
00:39:31,267 --> 00:39:35,196
Have you been to these
refugee camps? Have you
heard these stories?

866
00:39:35,267 --> 00:39:38,334
Congressman, I am required
to give you a briefing.

867
00:39:38,693 --> 00:39:40,285
Should I continue?

868
00:39:40,580 --> 00:39:42,009
No. Thank you.

869
00:39:53,155 --> 00:39:54,879
(SIGHING)

870
00:39:55,140 --> 00:39:59,962
You know, I had a neighbor,
growing up, with a name
right out of Dickens.

871
00:40:01,060 --> 00:40:03,131
Mr. Charles Hazard.

872
00:40:04,451 --> 00:40:07,485
And Mr. Hazard didn't like
the neighborhood dogs

873
00:40:07,555 --> 00:40:09,563
messing up his flower beds.

874
00:40:10,083 --> 00:40:11,872
One day, I heard
a bunch of yelling
from across the street,

875
00:40:11,940 --> 00:40:13,314
so I ran on over
to Mr. Hazard's,

876
00:40:13,379 --> 00:40:16,991
and there were about
15 grown-ups standing
around my dog, Teddy,

877
00:40:17,060 --> 00:40:20,800
who was writhing
on the ground
in obvious agony.

878
00:40:21,314 --> 00:40:23,103
Blood was pouring
out of his mouth.

879
00:40:23,170 --> 00:40:25,407
Mr. Hazard had
ground up a glass bottle

880
00:40:25,476 --> 00:40:28,608
and put it in a bowl
of dog food and
fed it to him.

881
00:40:30,243 --> 00:40:31,771
What did you do?

882
00:40:32,292 --> 00:40:35,259
Well, I got some gasoline
and burned down
his flower beds.

883
00:40:35,333 --> 00:40:37,666
But that wasn't
satisfying enough.

884
00:40:38,755 --> 00:40:42,236
And then I remembered,
Mr. Hazard was
an elected official.

885
00:40:42,307 --> 00:40:44,544
He was the head
of the town council.

886
00:40:44,611 --> 00:40:47,395
His reelection every two years
was a foregone conclusion.

887
00:40:47,461 --> 00:40:51,716
So come Election Day,
I drove over to
the black section of town.

888
00:40:51,780 --> 00:40:54,943
Now, these people
hadn't voted in any of
these elections, so...

889
00:40:55,011 --> 00:40:57,793
I was only 13,
but I had a farmer's license

890
00:40:59,267 --> 00:41:00,696
and I filled up my car
with black voters

891
00:41:00,772 --> 00:41:01,982
and drove them
to the polling place

892
00:41:02,052 --> 00:41:03,328
and then waited,
then drove them on home.

893
00:41:03,395 --> 00:41:06,211
But before they got out
of the car to vote

894
00:41:06,276 --> 00:41:11,198
I said, " I don't
mean to influence you,
but I think you should know

895
00:41:11,269 --> 00:41:14,715
"Mr. Charles Hazard
has intentionally
killed my dog."

896
00:41:17,027 --> 00:41:19,614
About 400 ballots were
cast in that election.

897
00:41:19,684 --> 00:41:22,173
I drove 96 of them
to the polls.

898
00:41:23,237 --> 00:41:25,244
Hazard lost by 16 votes.

899
00:41:28,677 --> 00:41:32,025
And that's the day
I fell in love
with America.

900
00:41:35,428 --> 00:41:37,152
What time do we land?

901
00:41:37,764 --> 00:41:39,707
7:30 a.m. In D.C.

902
00:41:40,388 --> 00:41:42,877
I want the CIA
in my office
at 10:00.

903
00:41:43,653 --> 00:41:46,075
Assistant Deputy Director
or higher.

904
00:41:46,470 --> 00:41:49,022
Tell them that if
I don't see someone
at 10:00,

905
00:41:49,092 --> 00:41:53,827
I'm gonna start docking
their allowance at a rate
of $1 million a minute.

906
00:41:54,021 --> 00:41:55,231
Yes, sir.

907
00:41:55,557 --> 00:41:56,931
And get me another
one of them, would you?

908
00:41:56,997 --> 00:41:57,945
(CLEARING THROAT)

909
00:41:58,885 --> 00:42:00,095
Yes, sir.

910
00:42:02,790 --> 00:42:04,677
AGENT PATRICK: The AKs,
RPG-7 grenade launchers

