their ears cleaned.

918
00:42:19,941 --> 00:42:22,210
The mules are getting
better health care
than the Afghans.

919
00:42:22,277 --> 00:42:25,439
AGENT WELLS: Plus, they're
gonna cost a little extra
if we want them pre-trained.

920
00:42:25,507 --> 00:42:26,970
To do what?
Walk over a mountain

921
00:42:27,044 --> 00:42:28,124
with ammunition
on their back.

922
00:42:28,197 --> 00:42:29,473
Aren't they born
with that instinct?

923
00:42:29,541 --> 00:42:32,126
I mean, isn't that
something they want
to do naturally?

924
00:42:32,197 --> 00:42:35,296
You think Afghanistan might,
one day, think about building
some fucking roads?

925
00:42:35,366 --> 00:42:37,056
Gust.
Yeah?

926
00:42:37,126 --> 00:42:39,013
I got something for you.

927
00:42:39,942 --> 00:42:41,283
I need you
to be specific...

928
00:42:41,350 --> 00:42:43,715
MARLA: The whole thing
has changed. Get your diary.
L'll show you.

929
00:42:43,779 --> 00:42:44,827
Okay.

930
00:42:46,020 --> 00:42:47,876
RECEPTIONIST: No problem.
Thank you.

931
00:42:49,349 --> 00:42:50,461
He should be here
any moment.

932
00:42:50,534 --> 00:42:53,086
Don't worry about me.
I'm fine.

933
00:42:54,535 --> 00:42:56,192
Good morning.
Good morning, Congressman.

934
00:42:56,261 --> 00:42:57,822
Welcome back.
Yeah. Marla.

935
00:42:57,894 --> 00:42:59,268
Welcome back.
Suzanne.

936
00:42:59,334 --> 00:43:00,739
Welcome back.

937
00:43:02,020 --> 00:43:03,003
Who are you?

938
00:43:03,078 --> 00:43:04,222
RECEPTIONIST:
This is Gust Avrakotos.

939
00:43:04,292 --> 00:43:05,983
He's come up from Langley
to bring you the information

940
00:43:06,053 --> 00:43:07,964
that you wanted.
Bonnie!

941
00:43:08,454 --> 00:43:09,402
Yes, sir?

942
00:43:09,478 --> 00:43:11,004
I said Assistant Deputy
Director or higher.

